The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Helpline for wealth managers

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Aug. 30: Birlasoft Limited , the IT arm of the CK Birla group of companies, has developed Birlasoft Advisor+ a software that enables wealth managers to profile customers, find out their risk taking capacities, do a wide range of portfolio analysis and make investment recommendations.

 With high net worth individuals growing at a rate of 14-15 per cent annually, wealth planning has become a big-ticket business and the software claims that it will act as a useful tool to do exactly that. We are trying to fill the gap, said N.K. Subramaniyam, senior vice-president, financial services group, Birlasoft Limited. 

 Apart from executing a transaction, the product covers the entire gamut of wealth management right from portfolio creation to tracking the investments and rebalancing the portfolio to meet a clients changing investment needs, he said. 




